<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Home Affairs Committee Inquiry into PCCs – Progress to Date</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">Written evidence from </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">Kevin Hurley, </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">P</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">olice and</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none"> Crime Commissioner for Surrey</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none"> [PCC Progress 0</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">8</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">]</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.72pt; padding-left:20.28pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">Effectiveness of commissioners in reducing crime and delivering an effective police service within their police force area</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">1.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">The role of a PCC is significant, substantial and wide-ranging. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> Although still early in its evolution, </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">it is already apparent that the creation of a</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> direct democratic link between the public and the police service that serves them has been a healthy step in the right direction for this country and a significant improvement on what came before. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">In considering the effectiveness of PCCs to date and into the future, I believe we must reflect carefully on what it is we base our judgement of police success. In my view, the public’s sense of safety is the key measure of the value of the authorities. I aspire towards a county where anyone can feel safe walking down any street at any time of day. Reducing crime is just one part of that. It also involves a strengthening confidence that the authorities </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">will</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> deal with our concerns and be there when we need them, not when it suits them. It involves restoring faith that the criminal justice system will tackle lawbreakers firmly and victims compassionately. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:uppercase">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">1.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">I am delighted to work with a Chief Constable, Lynne Owens, who lives and breathes the ethos and the mission of British policing. One who passionately believes in the relentless pursuit of criminals; in making sure that the police are there when people need them; and keeping people safe. In short, she believes in putting the public first. I back our Chief Constable and our police officers and staff to use their judgement and discretion to make the right decisions for the public. They are the professionals. I believe in their goodwill and their determination to make our society better. I trust them to do their jobs.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:uppercase">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">1.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">As Commissioner, it is my role to support the police and add value to their work for the public with the strategic decisions I make. Below, I outline some of the activities that my team and I have initiated during the first year in office to help improve the effectiveness of the police service – and the wider community safety partnership - in Surrey:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">By setting out the main principle of ‘Zero Tolerance’ in the Police and Crime Plan, I have set the scene in Surrey that we should </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">never</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> turn away from a problem. We should </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">always</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> aim to do the right thing for the public. We should </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">relentlessly pursue </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">the criminals and anti-social louts who blight our</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> county.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">Amongst my first actions was to extend </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">Chief Constable’s contract to ensure stability and continuity for Surrey Police leadership</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">.</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">I have appointed an Assistant Commissioner for victims and I am leading on the national project to move victim support governance and funding to PCCs</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">I have </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">allocated the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">Community Safety fund to back those groups and organisations that can help to deliver the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">People’s P</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">riorities in Surrey.  </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">So far, £225,000 in grant funding has been awarded, supporting 24 crime reduction and community safety initiatives. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">This has</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> include</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">d</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> online safety &amp; conduct advice for every pupil in Surrey’s state secondary schools; employment of an Independent Sexual Violence Advisor; support for the Youth Support Service Substance Misuse Team; and funding for a Manager for Surrey’s Young Witness Service. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">We cannot expect our police to get in harm’s way and protect the public without our backing.  I am active in standing up for our police and providing a voice for our officers where they </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">cannot speak up for themselves.  </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">I remain a strong critic of the cuts to Constables’ starting salaries and in Surrey we have set starting salaries at the maximum level we possibly can.  I have vehemently opposed </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">proposals to enable direct entry into po</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">licing at Superintendent level –</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> I want competent leaders who choose to put the public and victims first. By supporting</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> our police I am aiming to protect the discretionary goodwill and public spirit that is central to the success, and efficiency, of British policing. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">Like other forces, Surrey has been experiencing substantial budget cuts and financial challenges.  </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">I am working on a number of fronts to mitigate the impact of these cuts.</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">My Deputy PCC has been leading on a number of projects aimed at working in partnership to prevent crime.  He has set up and chairs a local Surrey Cybercrime Prevention network to reduce victims of cyber enabled crime.   He has also been working with partners to ensure that Junior Citizen programme</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">s are carried out across </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">Surrey, with the intent to ensure young people are aware of their roles and responsibilities as they become adults.</span><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:uppercase">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">1.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">Partnership is perhaps the most exciting frontier for Commissioners to explore. PCCs have a remit and a level of political influence not before seen at a county level. We are in a unique position to bring partner agencies together in the public interest and I have spent much of my first year in office meeting with those who have a part to play in improving the sense of safety in Surrey’s communities.   I am working with councils to promote better joint working between Safer Neighbourhood Teams and Local Authorities. Local authority staff who already have powers of enforcement, such as planning officers, environmental health officers and traffic wardens, will work together with police Safer Neighbourhood Teams in order to deal more effectively with the antisocial behaviour problems that the public consistently raise as concerns. The aim of this project is to deal with problems by making the most of all the legal powers the authoriti</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">es – police and councils – have</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> to tackle those causing persistent nuisance and concern to residents using the legal powers entrusted in us.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">1.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">By enforcing the law more quickly, consistently and strongly against anti-social behaviour wherever the authorities encounter it, we send out a clear message that selfish, antisocial and criminal behaviour will not be tolerated in our county. Our first joint enforcement team is planned to go live in January 2014. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:uppercase">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">1.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">Looking ahead, I would like to see Police and Crime Commissioners’ remit – and the direct democratic link with the public that they provide - extended across the criminal justice system. Local communities are detached from a criminal justice system overseen remotely from them and oblivious to their priorities. I can see significant advantages in those involved in the delivery of criminal justice being held to public account at a local level.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:uppercase">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">1.8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">For more details on my effectiveness, I attach the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">Police and Crime Plan</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">and</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">my first </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">Annual </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">Report.</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.72pt; padding-left:20.28pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">Role of commissioners in holding their chief constables to account</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:uppercase">2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">Holding the Chief Constable to account is a key statutory responsibility </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">and it is</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">important that both </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">I</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> and the wider public can see how Surrey Police is performing against the Police &amp; Crime Plan and that the Force is rightly and properly subject to oversight, scrutiny and accountability to ensure it is operating efficiently and effectively. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:uppercase">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">One of my first acts as PCC was to do away with numerical targets for the police force – the first in the country to do so. The target culture has had a negative impact on British policing over the last 20 years.  </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">Targets</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> provide reassurance to politicians but they mean very little to the wider public. They can lead to perverse incentives towards policing activity that satisfies performance managers and no-one else. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">2.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">No targets does not mean no accountability however. I </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">openly and constructively</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> scrutinise the Chief Constable and the force</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">I do not wish</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> to take an adversarial approach</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> nor </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">do I want</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> senior officers and staff to be spending time in unnecessary meetings. In holding the Chief Constable to account, </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">I don’t seek to fetter </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">her</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">operational independence or undermine her ability to direct and control the Force. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">Rather, I have sought to</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> strike a balance between effective oversight and scrutiny and allowing the Chief Constable to deliver the ‘day job’.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">2.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">Central to my oversight activities are</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">bi-monthly </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">management meetings.  </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">hes</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">e </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">management meetings </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">are webcast </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">live </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">so that public, media, partners and police can see how I </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">am holding the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">Chief C</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">onstable to account</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> and what progress is being made</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">I was the first, and until recently the only, PCC to webcast these meetings and bring about such a novel approach to transparency.  </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">Agendas </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">are set in advance and papers publish</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">ed on my website for all to see.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">2.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">In addition to this very public scrutiny, </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">and recognising that there is an equally important scrutiny role to be carried out on operationally or legally sensitive matters, </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">I meet privately with the Chief Constable at least every two weeks and more often as necessary</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">My staff also attend relevant Surrey Police meetings, such as their Crime Performance Board, to understand force performance in more detail. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">2.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">I am also in the process of setting up a bi-mo</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">nthly scrutiny panel.  </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">At this meeting I, my Deputy and Assistant PCCs will look at Surrey Police performance </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">in greater </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">depth where aspects of the Police and Crime </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">P</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">lan are not being met.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.72pt; padding-left:20.28pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">Role of police and crime panels in holding their commissioners to account</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">3.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">The first year of the new system of police governance has been a process of evolution for Panels as well as PCCs. We continue to learn as we go.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">3.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">I feel I have been </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">subject to robust and open scrutiny</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> by the Surrey Police and Crime Panel</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">.  I have attended 5 </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">public Panel meetings</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> in my first year as well as informal workshops and meetings.  I </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">have </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">present</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">ed on and answered</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> questions </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">about </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">my budget, the Surrey Police budget, pro</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">gre</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">ss against the Police and Crime Plan, how I have held the Chief Constable to account, collaboration and change </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">programmes as well as many other issues.  </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:uppercase">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">3.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">I hope to maintain a constructive relationship, </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">one which remains </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">focused on fulfilling our </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">duties</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> -</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">as defined in law -</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> in the best interest of the public.</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:uppercase">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.72pt; padding-left:20.28pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">Division of functions and staff between commissioners and chief constables following the Stage 2 transfers</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">4.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">I </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">have submitted </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">my </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">plan</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> for Stage 2</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> to the Home Secretary </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">which sets out my proposals for the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">division</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> of assets</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> and staf</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">f following Stage 2 transfer. The plan has the full support of the Chief Constable. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">In essence, nearly all police staff will be transferring to the employment of the Chief Constable, apart from a small team of PCC support staff, around </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">9</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> people (full-</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">ime equivalent</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">s).  I will retain ownership of </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">all </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">assets</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">, including</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> estates.  We will ensure a clear roles and </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">lines </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">of accountability through new governance documents.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">4.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">My view</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> is that</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">, post transfer,</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> the Chief Constable should be responsible for the delivery of policing and I will hold her to account for the totality of that delivery.  My focus will remain on my strategic and </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">representative</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> role while the Chief </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">onstable will focus on the delivery of operational policing with responsibility for the back office</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> services that support this.  </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">F</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">uture working arrangements between the Force and PCC must be a joint endeavour, focused upon improving outcomes for local people</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.72pt; padding-left:20.28pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">The role of commissioners in budget and precept setting</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">5.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">S</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">etting the budget and precept is one of my key roles and I am the main decision maker in that process.  </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">I have a very experienced Chief Finance Officer </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">(</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">CFO)</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> to brief me on the t</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">echnical detail budget setting</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">I have consulted on my draft budget and precept proposals </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">with public, victims and businesses.</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> I then work with Surrey Police and my CFO</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> to go through the policing priorities, government grant funding</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> and the</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> results of consultation to develop the budget and precept proposals to put forward to the Police and Crime Panel.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">5.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">In a climate of increasing austerity, we must make difficult decisions.  I make those decisions in the best interests of the public and in line with the priorities as expressed in the Police and Crime Plan.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:uppercase">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">5.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">I also have an important role in representing the interests of the public of Surrey in the national decisions that impact on our budget and precept. Surrey residents pay the highest precept for their policing in the country, because the county receives one of the lowest levels of Government grant. Other areas with similar crime rates receive as much as double the amount of funding per head of population as Surrey. I will be playing an active role in future discussions on a police funding formula which simply does not reflect the true costs of policing in this country and fails to allocate funding accurately on the basis of need.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.72pt; padding-left:20.28pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">The effectiveness of commissioners in promoting local policing priorities</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">6.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">From the very outset</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">, I have been</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> clear that the priorities of the public should dictate the direction and the style of policing in Surrey. Six ‘People’s Priorities’ form the basis for the Police and Crime Plan for Surrey. I the Chief Constable to account for delivery of and progress against that Plan which I believe will ultimately lead to a reduction in crime, anti-social behaviour and a better police service for local people and victims of crime.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">6.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">PCCs are visible and communicate </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">in </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">a way that Police Authorities were never able to. Recent research </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">has</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> demonstrated that over 60% of people have now heard of the PCC role. That compares to 7% who had heard of their Police Author</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">ity. This is a significant step </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">forward for local democracy and is something I hope to continue to build on throughout my time in office.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">6.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">Unlike Police Authorities, engagement, consultation and communication with the public are </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">in the DNA of the PCC role</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">. I am here to listen to their priorities and make sure they are reflected in the policing services they receive. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">To illustrate, my activities have included:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">A seri</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">es</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> of four engagement events in Surrey soon after I was elected and prior to setting my Police and Crime Plan </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">Holding a Crime Summit in each of the 11 Borough and Districts in Surrey during 2013/2014 including a PCC presentation on the People’s Priorities </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">Media articles, radio and TV appearances to promote the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">People’s Pr</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">iorities</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">Meetings with local council, criminal justice, voluntary sector and business partners to promote the priorities</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">Work with Surrey Police to ensure that the priorities are understood by all and promoted as </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">appropriate</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">Meetings with staff associations and senior police leaders to go through the priorities</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">Visits out ‘</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">on the ground’ to Surrey Police, </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">partners</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> and public.  This has undoubtedly had the greatest impact with the public in my role as PCC</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">, and has included meeting with</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> 800 people in local mosque, </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">with a </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">200 </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">strong </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">neighbourhood watch </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">group and speaking to </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">several hundred young people attending Surrey Youth Shout events. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.72pt; padding-left:20.28pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">Progress on establishing collaboration agreements with other commissioners, policing organisations and partners </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">7.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">Like many other police forces, Surrey Police needs to make large savings over the next few years.  </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">Surrey and Sussex have in the last few years been collaborating on a small number of specialist crime services.  Recently I have agreed with the PCC for Sussex, Katy Bourne, and the two Chief Constables, a vision for future: </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">“Surrey and Sussex Police working as one, operationally and organisationally to enhance and improve services for the public whilst reducing costs and responding to local needs”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">7.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">On 1 October 2013 Surrey and Sussex have moved towards a lead force model for collaborating in Specialist Crime and Operations with an Assistant Chief Constable in charge of these two commands.   We are currently reviewing Support Service functions to bring these together for the two forces over the next few years.   These changes will help make the savings needed in Surrey and Sussex whilst improving operational resilience.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">7.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">We are also working within Surrey with partners on an Emergency Services Collaboration project</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">, encouraging closer working between blue light services</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">.  This will be worked up alongside the Surrey/ Sussex collaboration plans. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:uppercase">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">7.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">I, with support from my office, am also taking a national lead role working </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">with other PCCs </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">on </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">the provision of victim support services to ensure that the proposed plans to transfer funding and governance of these services to PCC</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">s</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> are robust and will deliver the required level of support to victims. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:uppercase">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">7.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">The PCCs in the South East have also signed a deal with BT which will make 20% savings on telecoms over the next 7 years. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:uppercase">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">7.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">We also have a number of other local partnership projects and collaborations that we are working on including the development of Joint Law Enforcement between Surrey Police and Local Councils, a local Surrey Cyber Safe Partnership and taking a lead on Surrey partnership boards. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.72pt; padding-left:20.28pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:none">Transparency of and reporting by commissioners to date </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">8.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">I aim to be transparent in the work I do.  I publish all key decisions that I have made along with details of my salary and expenses as well as those for my deputy, assistant commissioner and salaries for all senior staff.   I publish gifts and hospitality, a register of interests and any matters of complaints or conduct. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">8.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">In </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">addition to my </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">webcast management meetings at which I </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">scrutinise the Chief Constable</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">,</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">I also publish a quarterly update on Surrey Police performance and progress being made against the Police and Crime Plan on my website. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:uppercase">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">8.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">I attend the Police and Crime Panel which is webcast and publishe</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">s its papers</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> for the public to view.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:uppercase">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">8.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">I am also a strong public advocate for the rights of whistleblowers in public services and the importance of a strong free press in providing an avenue for wrongdoing to be brought to public attention.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">Please </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">do</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none"> contact my office if you require any further information on my work. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">Kevin Hurley</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">Police an</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">d Crime Commissioner for Surrey</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; text-transform:none">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> Not printed</span></p></body></html>